{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":928,"text":"Everything is interconnected."},{"time":4012,"text":"As a Shinnecock Indian, I was raised to know this."},{"time":7538,"text":"We are a small fishing tribe"},{"time":9561,"text":"situated on the southeastern tip of Long Island"},{"time":12745,"text":"near the town of Southampton in New York."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15910,"text":"When I was a little girl,"},{"time":18380,"text":"my grandfather took me to sit outside in the sun on a hot summer day."},{"time":23728,"text":"There were no clouds in the sky."},{"time":27282,"text":"And after a while I began to perspire."},{"time":30453,"text":"And he pointed up to the sky, and he said,"},{"time":33979,"text":"\"Look, do you see that?"},{"time":36827,"text":"That's part of you up there."},{"time":38946,"text":"That's your water that helps to make the cloud"},{"time":41861,"text":"that becomes the rain that feeds the plants"},{"time":46134,"text":"that feeds the animals.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":49920,"text":"In my continued exploration of subjects in nature"},{"time":52912,"text":"that have the ability to illustrate the interconnection of all life,"},{"time":57328,"text":"I started storm chasing in 2008"},{"time":60029,"text":"after my daughter said, \"Mom, you should do that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":63897,"text":"And so three days later, driving very fast,"},{"time":70108,"text":"I found myself stalking a single type of giant cloud called the super cell,"},{"time":77368,"text":"capable of producing grapefruit-size hail"},{"time":81819,"text":"and spectacular tornadoes,"},{"time":83812,"text":"although only two percent actually do."},{"time":90118,"text":"These clouds can grow so big, up to 50 miles wide"},{"time":95262,"text":"and reach up to 65,000 feet into the atmosphere."},{"time":99328,"text":"They can grow so big, blocking all daylight,"},{"time":101702,"text":"making it very dark and ominous standing under them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106826,"text":"Storm chasing is a very tactile experience."},{"time":109728,"text":"There's a warm, moist wind blowing at your back"},{"time":113995,"text":"and the smell of the earth, the wheat, the grass, the charged particles."},{"time":120697,"text":"And then there are the colors in the clouds"},{"time":124094,"text":"of hail forming, the greens and the turquoise blues."},{"time":129284,"text":"I've learned to respect the lightning."},{"time":132562,"text":"My hair used to be straight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134696,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":136120,"text":"I'm just kidding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137744,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":139886,"text":"What really excites me about these storms"},{"time":143062,"text":"is their movement, the way they swirl and spin and undulate,"},{"time":147279,"text":"with their lava lamp-like mammatus clouds."},{"time":151297,"text":"They become lovely monsters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154029,"text":"When I'm photographing them,"},{"time":156562,"text":"I cannot help but remember my grandfather's lesson."},{"time":160295,"text":"As I stand under them,"},{"time":162287,"text":"I see not just a cloud,"},{"time":164494,"text":"but understand that what I have the privilege to witness"},{"time":167377,"text":"is the same forces, the same process in a small-scale version"},{"time":171827,"text":"that helped to create our galaxy, our solar system, our sun"},{"time":178145,"text":"and even this very planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182703,"text":"All my relations. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185160,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}